²quae pariter Deo serviebant: Augustino had established a uunnery at Hippo Regius of which his sister was prioress and to which the daughters oi his brother Navigius also belonged. This seems to have been the first nunnery in Africa, though later than those founded by J erome and :Paula in Palestine in 384 After the death oi Augustine’s sister in 423 dissension arose among the nuns over the appointment of Felicitas as her successor. Augustine wrote them a stetu letter oi rebuke and, improving the opportunity, laid down a code oi strict rules ior their conduct: Ep. ccx1.
